{
  "stem": "7337.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He knew exactly what was happening, but nobody-- nobody-- admitted it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Since the archives of those days are being made public-- I mean, if you read Anthony Eden, if you read Roosevelt, they knew exactly what was going on.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I mean, Roosevelt had a secretary of the treasury who was a Jew, Morgenthau, who begged of him to-- to let Jews come into America.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He said no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Britain wouldn't take any, except there was-- in 1938, they allowed in the-- what is called the Kindertransport.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They allowed children under 16.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I think they took in three-odd thousand.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But parents had to say goodbye to them, and were likely not to see them again.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] But that's the only organized lot of Jews that went into-- into England.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] there was no-- nowhere to go for people [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] legally.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And the French didn't help, the French Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] What did help was that my father had money.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It's always a different thing when-- when you have money.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I mean, we lived in comfort.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "We had a-- a beautiful apartment near the Eiffel Tower.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "My mother had to be operated again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And in fact, there was a-- from a humanitarian point of view, she wanted to have the second operation from-- performed by the professor who had done her first operation in Germany.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And the French professor who was looking after her said, all right, bring him out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We'll go into the theater together, and when it comes to it, I'll cut the wound open.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And then I'll step aside, and he can do the operation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "That was, of course, highly illegal.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
